Subject: Re: [T2] MPH to RPM for 82 Vanagon

On Wednesday, August 11, 2004, at 10:09AM, Kevin Smith <blue82vw(-at-)hotmail.com> wrote:

>Has anyone ever calculated the RPMs for different speeds and gear 
>combinations?  OR is there a formula that someone can point me to?  I'm 
>using the stock tire size 185R14s and I don't have a tach.

MPH = RPM * TIRE HEIGHT INCHES / GEAR RATIO / R&P / 336

For example: 3400 RPM * 26 / 0.89 (4th) / 4.571 / 336 = 65 MPH

